'''红心乐团'''（{{lang-en|'''Heart'''}}）是于1970年在[[美国|美国]][[西雅图|西雅图]]组成的[[摇滚樂|搖滾]]乐团<ref name=believer07>Kelly, Maura [http://www.believermag.com/issues/200708/?read=interview_wilson ''Interview with Nancy Wilson''] {{Wayback|url=http://www.believermag.com/issues/200708/?read=interview_wilson |date=20210210212213 }}, The Believer, August 2007. Retrieved 2008-10-01.</ref><ref name=acousticguitar>Bergman, Julie [http://www.acousticguitar.com/issues/ag81/ag81.shtml ''Guitar Queen of Heart''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120128014617/http://www.acousticguitar.com/issues/ag81/ag81.shtml |date=2012-01-28 }}, cover story, Acoustic Guitar, September 1999, No. 81.</ref><ref name=annieDVD>Wilson, Ann. ''Dreamboat Annie Live'', DVD interview 2007.</ref><ref name=FisherRoger07>Fisher, Roger. Solo acoustic show, Q&A. 2007 ''It was a really magical relationship, it was uncanny. Living up in Vancouver BC for 5 years, putting Heart together up there''.</ref><ref name=FisherRoger08>Fisher, Roger. Interview 2008.{{Nonspecific|date=October 2008}}</ref><ref name=Circus77>Loder, Kurt. ''Making Music to the Northern Lights'', ''[[Circus_(magazine)|Circus Magazine]]''. November 1977. Roger Fisher on brother Mike Fisher: ''Then he moved to Canada, we got Ann, she met my brother, they fell in love, and so we moved up to Canada too, and put the band together up there about six years ago''.</ref><ref name=LQTP1>Little Queen tour program: ''In 1972, the core of Heart came together in Vancouver, B.C''.</ref><ref name=LQTP2>Little Queen tour program: ''In 1974, two years after Roger, Steve and Ann had moved to Vancouver, Nancy left school and joined them''.</ref><ref name=KWSU>''The Second Ending''. A [http://www.kwsu.org/KWSU_NWPR/Coverage/KWSU.aspx KWSU-TV] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727011708/http://www.kwsu.org/KWSU_NWPR/Coverage/KWSU.aspx |date=2011-07-27 }}, Pullman, WA, television show first broadcast on April 9, 1976. Ann Wilson speaks from the stage and says "''We only have time for one more I think, so we're gonna do a song that, um, was our first single up in Canada. Oh by the way, we're from Canada. We're from Vancouver BC, in case you haven't heard this yet. We're just starting to ooze down across the border now you see''".</ref>，有着[[硬摇滚|硬摇滚]]和[[重金屬樂|重金屬樂]]及[[民間音樂|民間音樂]]影响。此乐团虽历经不少组员改变， 但两姐妹[[安·威爾森|安·威爾森]]和[[南希·威爾森_(搖滾音樂家)|南希·威爾森]]始终是此乐团的重要成员。于80年代，他们的歌曲更是美国音乐排行榜上常客。90年代后，鮮少繼續在樂壇進行公演，但至今還有持續發行新的專輯。近年則投入乳癌防治和支援非洲貧民的活動。

到目前為止紅心樂團已在全球銷售超過3500萬張唱片，其中包括在美國銷售超過2250萬張的唱片。他們在1970年代、80年代、90年代和2010年代在[[公告牌二百強專輯榜|告示牌200大專輯榜]]上擁有前10名多張的專輯，而在[[VH1|VH1]]的“100位偉大的硬搖滾藝術家”中排名第57位。他們於2013年入選[[搖滾名人堂|搖滾名人堂]]。<ref>{{cite web |last=Valby |first=Karen |url=http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/12/11/rock-and-roll-hall-of-fame-rush-public-enemy/ |title=Public Enemy, Rush, Heart, Donna Summer to be inducted into Rock and Roll Hall of Fame | The Music Mix | EW.com |publisher=Music-mix.ew.com |date= |accessdate=2012-12-25 |archive-date=2014-10-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141025123650/http://music-mix.ew.com/2012/12/11/rock-and-roll-hall-of-fame-rush-public-enemy/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author= |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bnpvkn01y1c |title=Rock And Roll Hall Of Fame Inducts Rush With Heart, King, Newman, Public Enemy, Summer |publisher=YouTube |date=2013-04-19 |accessdate=2013-05-14 |archive-date=2020-03-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309070221/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bnpvkn01y1c |dead-url=no }}</ref>

